attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the middle shelf and the first leg. But he places them in the wrong way, the instructor indicates the student to rotate the leg and after some corrections the student is able to start screwing the first leg to the middle shelf. Once he learns the correct way to assemble the first leg, he continues with the second, third and fourth leg, screwing them all to the middle shelf. Then the instructor asks the student to assemble the top shelf, but he isn't able to do it, so the instructor gives the instructions to correctly place and attach the top shelf. When the student finds the correct way to place the top shelf, he starts screwing each of the four legs to the top shelf. When the furniture is assembled and all the screws are in place, the instructor asks the student to tighten all the screws on the middle and top shelf.
